@startuml fig-rip-loop
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title RIP Count-to-Infinity Problem and Mitigations

participant "Router R1" as R1 #E3F2FD
participant "Router R2" as R2 #E3F2FD
participant "Router R3" as R3 #E3F2FD

== NORMAL STATE ==

R1 -> R2 : "Network Z: hops=1"
R2 -> R3 : "Network Z: hops=2"

== R1–Z LINK FAILS ==

R1 ->x R1 : link to Z goes down

R2 -[#E53935]> R1 : "Network Z: hops=3"\n(learned from R3)
R1 -[#E53935]> R3 : "Network Z: hops=4"\n(learned from R2)
R3 -[#E53935]> R2 : "Network Z: hops=5"\n(loop continues)

...

R2 -[#E53935]> R1 : "Network Z: hops=16"\n(infinity — unreachable)

== CONVERGENCE (SLOW) ==

legend right
  After the failure, R2 and R3 falsely
  believe Z is still reachable via each other.
  Metrics grow until reaching 16 (infinity).
  Mitigations: split horizon, route poisoning,
  holddown timers and flush timers.
endlegend
@enduml
